# /etc/default/soundsync — SoundSync appliance configuration
#
# SoundSync's daemon runs as a systemd *user* service inside one user's
# PipeWire session. For a headless appliance, that user needs "linger"
# enabled so the daemon starts at boot without anyone logging in, and the
# package must know whose WirePlumber to restart after writing the A2DP
# config at install time.
#
# By default the postinst auto-detects the sole human login account
# (a single passwd entry with uid >= 1000 and a real login shell). If your
# box has zero or several such accounts, the auto-detect is skipped and you
# must name the appliance user here.
#
# Uncomment and set SOUNDSYNC_USER to the appliance user, e.g.:
#SOUNDSYNC_USER=mark
#
# NOTE: the variable is deliberately named SOUNDSYNC_USER (not USER). The
# postinst runs under "sudo apt install", where the ambient $USER is "root";
# a plain USER= here would be indistinguishable from that inherited value and
# would wrongly pin the appliance to root. SOUNDSYNC_USER cannot collide with
# any ambient environment variable, so when it is left unset the postinst
# falls through to the sole-human auto-detect instead of selecting root.
#
# After editing, run:   sudo dpkg-reconfigure soundsync
#   (or)                sudo loginctl enable-linger <user>
